API_Description: Navigates to a specific annotation within the PDF document.
API_Description_Reason: The method name 'goToAnnot' suggests functionality related to navigating or jumping to a specific annotation within the document.
Returns: A boolean indicating whether the navigation to the annotation was successful.
Returns_Reason: Navigation methods typically return a boolean to indicate success or failure of the operation.

nPageNum.description: The 0-based index of the page containing the annotation to navigate to.
nPageNum.description_reason: Page numbers are commonly used to specify the location of content within a document.
nPageNum.type_reason: Page numbers are typically represented as numbers.

cAnnotName.description: The name or identifier of the annotation to navigate to.
cAnnotName.description_reason: Annotations are often identified by a unique name or ID within a document.
cAnnotName.type_reason: Names or identifiers are usually represented as strings.
